org.orgName: The District Court of the United States

div1.p: IN THE UNITED STATE DISTRICT, WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.

Comes now King Dykeman, respondent named in the writ of habeas corpus issued in the above entitled action, and moves the court for an order quashing the writ of habeas corpus issued herein, dismissing the above entitled motion and remanding the petitioner above named to the custody of the Juvenile Detention Home in King County, Washington, on the ground and for the reason that the petition in this action fails to state facts suffcuent to entitle petitioner to any relief
Alfred H Laudin Frank P. Helsell Attorneys for Respondent.
IN THE U.S. DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER IF THE APPLICATION OF GLADYS FREDRIKA FUSON FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS
FILED INTHE U.S. District Court Western District of washington Oct 27 1916 FRANK L CROSBY Clerk by Edw Lakin Deputy
ALFRED H. LUNDIN FRANK P. HELSELL 432 Court Hourse, Seattle, Wash. Attorneys for Respondednt.
